395984.05 - 8.04 = 395976.01  Today, short and surprisingly fast. Cats woke me up before 6 o'clock in the morning and the three of them wished only to go out to the field ... but please! I just looked at the airly readings - 180% smog, dark ... and somehow I said that instead of panting in the mask I prefer to hug my wife (͡ ° ͜ʖ ͡ °) I woke up only at 8:00! Almost 7 hours of sleep ...  I accepted the fact that I will not run today - record early, because at 10:00 I had to start a great family breakfast and then it was time to gather for a trip ... However, it turned out that, however, it will be possible to save less than an hour - I quit to my wife that I'm flying and I jumped on a short, eight-kilometer route. Smog was already thinning - it was above 100% of the norm, but I saw that there is a downward trend, it starts to blow strongly, and besides, I absolutely did not want to run in the mask. Warm, 9 ° C - so of course, short pants and t-shirt. I was expecting it to be poor - after a rather hearty breakfast it is rather hard to run ... However, after the first kilometer it turned out that it is not that bad at all. I turned up the screw and it turned out that the further the better - at every kilometer I stopped a few dozen and a few seconds against the standard tempo of 5: 00 / km ᕙ (⇀‸↼ ") ᕗ  Of course, I was waiting back uphill, but as it turned out - the right motivation does the miracles (ʘ‿ʘ) I promised to come back before noon and I was so upright that despite the hills I kept up the pace and got ahead of time keeping the average rate of 4:45 min / km (͡ ° ͜ʖ ͡ °)  I know the distance of a tyciutka, but I am in shock that after breakfast managed to get such a result ... We'll see what comes out tomorrow, because the forecasts are quite uninteresting - rain, snow, around zero degrees, wind ... Hmm sounds encouraging ( ͡º ͜ʖ͡º)  Now it's time to go for a walk with your family - plans for a trip from Kościuszko Mound to Pilsudski Mound (.◕‿‿◕.) I have been having a relocation for a few days, which is very intense with my husband. There are many pluses but also a lot of negative points about this idea. Shortly about us: lvl 28 and 29 + yearly baby. We live in Suwalki, we grew up here, then studied in larger cities and for almost 5 years again Suwalki. Rent + PLN 750. Cities to which we can move to Krakow or Katowice (husband's work).  Pros of moving out: - more entertainment / concerts / restaurants, we like it very much and in Suwalki it is not - easy access to various types of activities (horse riding, shooting range, etc.) - better schools (future daughter) - living in a large city gives you great opportunities to develop a passion in your child, to which we as children had limited access - close in the mountains :) - it's easier to find jobs in my industry - the mentality of people in Suwalkach is very overwhelming - it's far from Suwalk  Disadvantages of moving out: - far from the family :( - it's hard for us to make new friends, here we have a few, but some friends, there will be no one and will not be able to meet someone - Suwalki have nice surroundings (greenery, forests, lakes), with which it's hard to leave - there are traffic jams in a big city, a long way is going from one end of the city to the other - not air, smog - high prices of real estate, both rental and purchase - and again, fuck, far from the family :(  As you can see the pluses are as much as minus ... on one side we choke on here and on the other we are afraid to leave everything and leave.
